notes: >
  Built per today's strategist plan (mail-merge-2026-06-28.md): one enterprise-down
  "alternative" page (Outreach.io), one head-to-head comparison completing the
  gmass/yamm/mailmeteor triangle (GMass vs Mailmeteor), one decision-stage how-to
  (Gmail mail merge from a Google Docs template), and one optimization how-to that
  extends the pos-1 subject-lines cluster (A/B test subject lines from Google Sheets).
  All four are root-level Jekyll .md with permalink:/slug/, single content H1, top+bottom
  CTA to /mail-merge-for-gmail-and-sheets/ (never GPT for Sheets), concrete workflow steps,
  worked examples, internal links to existing built pages, FAQ + FAQPage JSON-LD.
  The Outreach.io and GMass-vs-Mailmeteor pages carry visible non-affiliation disclaimers
  and dated/factual ("as of June 2026"), non-defamatory framing (no "better than"; explicit
  scope notes that the product has no contact database/dialer/CRM). The Google-Docs-template
  and A/B-test pages include consent/deliverability cautions (permissioned contacts, honest
  subject lines, clear sender identity/opt-out, Gmail/Workspace sending limits, test sends).
  All 4 slugs re-verified FREE on disk before authoring (no collisions; parked fallbacks
  unused). Post-build verification caught that {{First name}}/{{Company}}/{{Renewal date}}
  merge-field examples with spaces were breaking Liquid (hard exception on the Docs-template
  page); wrapped each page body in {% raw %}...{% endraw %} and rebuilt clean, then confirmed
  the placeholders render literally live and no raw tags leaked.
  Only the 4 intended page files (commit e02fa99) plus this marker were staged/committed;
  unrelated untracked files from a concurrent GPT-for-Sheets builder
  (clay-alternative-*, *-google-sheets-ai.md, deepseek/grok-api-key-*, .claude/launch.json)
  were left untouched.
